\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 41. P. julica} E. Mayer, {\i Phyton} ({\i Austria}){\b  9}: 301 (1961). Like {\b 40} but leaf-segments toothed; bracts densely villous, the upper ones 3-lobed; calyx villous; corolla up to 18 mm; capsule equalling calyx.{\i  Dry pastures and screes; calcicole. • S.E. Alps. }Au It Ju.
