\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 44. P. rostratospicata} Crantz,{\i  Stirp. Austr.} ed. 2,{\b  2}: 317 (1769) ({\i P. incarnata} Jacq., non L.). Stem 15-45 cm, ascending to erect, glabrous below, densely pubescent above. Leaves glabrous, lanceolate, pinnatisect with pinnatifid segments. Flowers in a rather lax spike; bracts hairy, with 3 linear-lanceolate lobes. Calyx hairy; teeth lanceolate, acute, entire or toothed. Corolla up to 13 mm, pink to purplish-red; tube about as long as calyx; beak long; lower lip glabrous. Capsule ovoid, apiculate, exceeding calyx. 2n = 16.{\i  Alpine pastures. • Alps; one station in E. Pyrenees.} Au Ga Ge He It Ju.
\par

