\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. P. rostratocapitata} Crantz, {\i Stirp. Austr.} ed. 2, {\b 2}: 320 (1769) ({\i P. rostrata} L. pro parte). Stem 5-20 cm, ascending, glabrous except for 1 or 2 lines of hairs. Leaves glabrous, often tinged with purple, oblong-lanceolate, 2-pinnatisect with oblong, entire or serrulate segments. Flowers in a capitate raceme; bracts similar to cauline leaves. Calyx glabrous or slightly pubescent on the veins; teeth foliose, lanceolate, crenate, recurved at apex. Corolla up to 25 mm, pink to purplish-red; tube slightly exceeding calyx; lower lip ciliate, at least at anthesis. Filaments of longer stamens sparsely pubescent to subglabrous. Capsule ovoid-oblong, apiculate, exceeding calyx. 2n = 16.{\i  Alpine pastures and screes; usually calcicole. • E. Alps, mountains of N.W. Jugoslavia.} Au Ge He It Ju.
